The paper deals with decoding of low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of linear programming in decoding also suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper presents bounds on thresholds, which is a topic in statistical learning theory (cs.LG) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of ensembles of codes suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.SI).
